2. This puts them upon a diligent ſearch after the provocation: they conclude on this, that there is blame in them; God would not have ſo deſerted them, if they had not ſome way prevaricated: this therefore they muſt find out, and they are in great anxiety of mind till they can come at it; 
                     •
                  hey cry out as he, Job 10.2. ſhew me wherefore thou contendeſt with me; and they look into every corner of their ſoul, to find out the Achan. David therefore in this trouble of his, runs up to the cauſe of it, viz. his carnal confidence, verſe 6.
